 <!-- Introduction -->
 <!-- The introduction should start as shown: -->
 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     representation of information needed to describe composition aspects of
     shape elements, by introducing new relationships and shape element,
     that is defined as composition of other shape elements.
   </p>
 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
      <li>identification of an association between shape elements, specifying that one shape element is a boundary or a portion of boundary of another shape element;</li>
      <li>identification of an association between shape elements, that associates shape element to a second shape element, to which the first shape element is constituent;</li>
      <li>identification of an association between shape elements, specifying that one shape element is composed of second shape element;</li>
      <li>identification of an association between shape elements, in which the associated shape elements are located in relation to each other;</li>
      <li>identification of shape element, that is composed of other constituent shape elements;</li>
      <li>items within the scope of application module <module_ref linkend="shape_property_assignment:1_scope">Shape property assignment</module_ref>, ISO/TS 10303-1032.</li>
   </inscope>

